		<P>
		According to a report in <em>Texas Highways</em> magazine, the final section of US 75 from 
		Buffalo to Streetman was extremely dangerous. Heavy traffic and the substandard design of US 75
		contributed to a high fatality rate. The completion of the final section in 1971 was 
		widely hailed as a huge safety improvement on the Texas highway system.
		
		<P>
		 These photos were taken on the Sunday of Thanksgiving weekend, which is why the traffic was so heavy.
		 Normally this is a pleasant drive with plenty of highway for each motorist.
